headline: Delta Air Lines (NYSE:DAL) Sees Net Income Rise To US$240M In Q1 Earnings Report
summary: Delta Air Lines (NYSE:DAL) recently saw its share price rise by 35% over the past month, a significant move amidst executive and board changes as well as a quarterly dividend declaration. The first-quarter earnings report, showing a rise in net income to $240 million and a basic EPS of $0.37, may have bolstered investor confidence. On the broader market front, stock movements were influenced by wider economic discussions, including U.S.-China trade talks and unchanged Federal Reserve interest...

headline: Delta, Korean Air to buy 25% stake in Canada's WestJet
summary: Delta will invest $330 million for a 15% stake and Korean Air will inject $220 million for a 10% interest.  The U.S. airline also plans to sell and transfer a 2.3% stake in WestJet to its joint venture partner, Air France-KLM, for $50 million.
